A propempticon to the poet Mevius, hated by Horace and the circle to which he belonged. Vergil has secured immortality for Mevius and his associate Bavius by his verses E. 3, 90 s. qui Bavium non odit, amet tua carmina, asem}- Ι atque idem iungat vulpes et mulgeat hircos. The ill-nature of Horace's poem should be compared with the good wishes in the propempticon addressed to Vergil C. 1, 3.
